args: Hey, master! Is it that castle?!
There is no need to shout, Wu Kong.\nI can hear you perfectly well.
Well, if it isn't Wu Kong and Xuan Zang!
It's good to see you both.
I am pleased to see you doing well,\nPrince—and I thank you again for\nall of your recent assistance.
We had some business nearby,\nand so dropped in to offer greetings.
We only deal in one kind of business,\nfriend: Qilin relics!
Those are the potentially dangerous items\nleft behind by ancient members of the\nQilin, right? Did you find one nearby?
We sure did! Or at least, we know there's\none around here SOMEWHERE, so we\ndecided to swing by and track it down.
In that case, you should make our castle\nyour base of operations! That's okay,\nright, {player_name}?
Niiice! Okay, Luca, time to give me the\nten-cent tour of your digs.
While it is most gracious indeed of you to\noffer, this is hospitality we cannot accept.
In the prosecution of our mission as\nsealers, we make use of the relics\nwe seek to lock away.

The huge power of those relics is often
beyond the ken of our current environs.
Thus, any who would wield such power
must take leave of the world at large.
I am afraid we cannot lend our efforts\nto your fight, {player_name}.
And as we cannot do so, I cannot permit\nus to impose upon your hospitality.
Actually, not everyone who lives\nat the castle fights for us.
Yeah, some of 'em just treat the castle as\none big crash pad.
I don't want to force the issue on you,\nbut if you aren't fully rested and ready,\ncouldn't that hinder your mission?
C'mon, master! Let's crash on their couch!
What you say does bear SOME merit...
Very well. In that case, we shall take you\nup on your most generous offer.
Oh, thank you so very much,\nPrince {player_name}!
If you weren't there, there's no telling\nWHAT might've happened!
How can we ever repay you?
That won't be necessary. You and your\npeople are welcome to stay here at the\ncastle for as long as you need.
Not with me, no. I was merely wondering\nabout those villagers over there.
Yeah, the Empire came blowin' through\nand razed their town to the ground,\nso we're givin' 'em a place to stay.
Are there other such refugees here?

Oh, we got refugees up the wazoo,
unfortunately. The Empire's been real
busy lately, and the prince ain't the
type'a guy what to turn anybody away.
*sigh* We wandered around all day,\nand didn't find a single Qilin relic.
Such steady, measured investigation is\nthe duty of a sealer. It is something to\nbe appreciated, not complained about.
Yeah, but I'm tiiiiiired! Can't we call it\na day or something, master?
I suppose we HAVE been going for a while.\nAlso, if we're out too late, it might be\ntroublesome for the people of the castle.
Niiice! Oh man, I wonder what kinda\ngrub Cleo whipped up today...?
You partake far too readily of their\nhospitality, Wu Kong. I would have you...\nHold a moment. What is that?
Keep going, everyone!\nThe Halidom is just ahead!
I won't make it...\nDon't worry about me. Keep going!
This is as far as you go, rebels!\nWe're not letting you reach your\nprecious traitor prince's castle!
The Sealer's Code forbids our interference.\nWe cannot take sides in this dispute.
You lot made trouble for the Empire,\nand now you'll face the Empire's\npunishment!

Clap these fools in irons and take them
to the work camp, men! They'll toil until
they beg for death...then toil some more!
Bwaaa ha ha ha!
Come, Wu Kong. We are going.
No! We can't just ignore those people!
I mean, I get that the Sealer's Code\nforbids interference or whatever, but it\ncan't possibly mean for us to ignore THIS!
Ah. I fear you have misunderstood me.\nWhen I said we were going, I meant that\nwe were going to free those villagers.
To break the Sealer's Code is dire indeed.
But sealer or not, to do nothing in the\nface of such suffering cannot be the\nproper course of action!
Then let's get to work, master!
The tyranny of this Empire is far beyond\nwhat I had imagined possible.
And as a denizen of this world, I will not\nstand by and allow them to continue\nsuch wanton cruelty unhindered.
I do indeed. We will lend our strength\nto the cause of {player_name}!
